rComments: Greta is a great prof! She is clear in what she wants from the assignments she gives and she lets students choose topics that interest them. She is a thorough marker and is very fair. I would take another class with her in a heart beat (and I have taken two already)!

Greta is an AMAZING professor. She is incredibly kind, understanding, and compassionate. She is also extremely knowledgeable about her area of expertise-- the book and print history and culture. I would love to take another course with Greta, but my schedule does not allow for it, sadly.

Greta Golick is a wonderful teacher. She is highly knowledgeable and goes out of her way to make the classes interesting and fun. I learned a lot and discovered a new interest: rare books. I am thrilled to have taken her class!

Although this professor makes class interesting with lots of hands on activities, field trips, etc, when she marks she's really tough (despite  encouraging you "to have fun" with the paper--deceiving).  She also does not provide you with feedback and you have to chase her down. She's a new professor.
